<TITLE> Baitul Mukarram Khatib laid to rest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)  Baitul Mukarram Khatib Moulana Ubaidul Huq was buried at Azimpur Graveyard Sunday. The national mosque's chief cleric died at the age of 79 from natural causes in Dhaka late Saturday night, his family said. Huq was born in Zakiganj Upazila in Sylhet in 1928. Huq fell sick at the Iranian Cultural Centre in Dhanmondi from where he was rushed to Medinova Hospital in an Iranian Embassy vehicle, the Khatib's son, Shahidul Huq, told reporters. The Khatib, who suffered from diabetes, was then taken to Bangladesh Medical College Hospital in Dhanmondi before being transferred to Labaid Hospital where he died at 11:15pm. According to his son, Huq had been suffering from a respiratory problem in his final days. The Khatib's body was kept at Baitul Mukarram Mosque for mourners to pay their last respects from 10 am Sunday. Huq is survived by his four sons and seven daughters. The religious leader's Namaz-e-Janaza was held at the National Eidgah. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed, former president HM Ershad, advisers Mainul Hosein and ASM Matiur Rahman, Mayor Sadek Hossain Khoka and army chief General Moeen U Ahmed joined the janaza. M Fazlur Rahman, director general of the Islamic Foundation said the government would appoint the next Khatib of the national mosque. bdnews24.c
